Text: The past week has been quite productive in organising how to approach studio project #1.
It started with a meeting between all the Shift students to arrange into group which eventually led to Riri, Roro and myself joining the Ocean Browser "Data wrangling and User Dashboard" project.
After this was confirmed, we broke off into a side meeting and had a quick discussion about what each others interests are in the project and the roles we might be most interested in taking on.
We then took some time to look deeper into Ocean Browser itself and what exactly they are working to see where our project fits in to their goals.
On Thursday, we had a Zoom meeting and brainstormed some questions to ask Rodney about the requirements of the project.
The goal is to have these be finalised and well defined before the meeting on Tuesday.
This was a very productive introduction to the project.

On Saturday, we had a Teams meeting we further discussed our roles and got on the same page about our thoughts on the scope of the project and discussed the overview of how we might go about accomplishing sub tasks.
We then talked more about the interview and decided that I would take the lead on requirements elicitation with Rodney in the meeting.
We then took a look at Roro's react dataviz prototype which was great.
This meeting was productive and Microsoft Teams seems to be the workflow tool of choice for the team.
Also Trello, google docs and zoom is being used.
Overall i am happy with the group cooperation that we have had so far.

I would say that up till now I would not change anything about our ways of operating for this part of the project, however I hope we can use github to share work on the repository for the project and have mentioned this to the group.
The biggest thing I learned last week was the difference between graphQL and restAPIs and a little bit about how d3, canvas js, and react works.
I am looking forward to continuing to learn how this works and making something with it in the coming weeks.

For this week the goal is to understand much more clearly what Rodney would like us to produce for Ocean Browser by asking good questions in the interview, then have a productive meeting to assign more clear roles on how to complete the project to his specifications with good results.
